{{Campaignbox Vietnam War}}
==March==

;March
All Thai troops from the Royal Thai Army Volunteer Force leave the country.<ref name= "Stanton p. 271">{{harvnb|Stanton|2003|p=271}}</ref>

;March 30 - October 22, 1972
The [[Easter Offensive]], officially, the '''Nguyen Hue Offensive''' and also ('''Chi<U+1EBF>n d<U+1ECB>ch Xu<U+00E2>n h<U+00E8> 1972''' in Vietnamese) was a military campaign conducted by the [[People's Army of Vietnam]] (PAVN, the regular army of North Vietnam) against the [[Army of the Republic of Vietnam]] (ARVN, the regular army of South Vietnam) and the [[United States]] between 
;March 30-May 1 
The [[First Battle of Qu<U+1EA3>ng Tr<U+1ECB>]] resulted in the first major victory for the [[North Vietnamese Army]] during the [[Easter Offensive|Nguyen Hue Offensive]] of 1972.

==April==
;April 4<U+2013>7 

The [[Battle of Loc Ninh]] was a major battle fought during the [[North Vietnam]]ese [[Easter Offensive]] and lasted from 4<U+2013>7 April 1972. [[Loc Ninh]] was a small district town in [[Binh Long Province]], approximately {{convert|60|mi|km}} north of the capital of [[Saigon]].

;April 13 <U+2013> July 20 
The [[Battle of An L<U+1ED9>c]] was a major battle that lasted for 66 days and culminated in a decisive victory for [[South Vietnam]]. In many ways, the struggle for [[An L<U+1ED9>c]] in 1972 was an important battle of the war, as South Vietnamese forces halted the [[North Vietnam]]ese advance towards [[Saigon]].

;April 19 
The [[Battle of Dong Hoi]] was a clash between [[United States Navy]] warships and three [[North Vietnam]]ese air force [[MiG-17F]] [[fighter bomber]]s, several [[torpedo boat]]s and shore batteries on April 19, 1972 during the [[Vietnam War]]. 

==May==	

;May 2 <U+2013> July 1 
The [[Battle of Kontum]] was fought during [[North Vietnam]]'s [[Easter Offensive|Nguyen Hue Campaign or the Easter Offensive]]. 

==June==
;June 3<U+2013>12 
[[Operation Thunderhead]] was a highly classified combat mission conducted by [[United_States_Navy_SEALs#SEAL_Teams|U.S. Navy SEAL Team One]] and [[Underwater demolition team|Underwater Demolition Team (UDT)]]-11 in 1972. The mission was conducted off the coast of North Vietnam to rescue two U.S. airmen said to be escaping from a prisoner of war prison in [[Hanoi]].<ref name= "Luckett-Byler p. 187">{{harvnb|Luckett|Byler|2005| p=187}}</ref>

;June 28 <U+2013> September 16 
The [[Second Battle of Quang Tri]] ({{lang-vi|Th<U+00E0>nh c<U+1ED5> Qu<U+1EA3>ng Tr<U+1ECB>}}) began on June 28 and lasted 81 days until September 16, 1972, when the [[Army of the Republic of Vietnam]] (ARVN) defeated the [[North Vietnam]]ese at the ancient citadel of [[Qu<U+1EA3>ng Tr<U+1ECB>]] and recaptured most of the province.

==December==
;December 14

All members of the [[New Zealand Defence Force|New Zealand armed forces]] are withdrawn from South Vietnam.<ref name= "Jessup p. 523">{{harvnb|Jessup|1998|p=523}}</ref>

